Creature Handlers of SWG</a><br>The place to go for all of you Creature Handler Questions with no flames from Combat Classes!<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reinyawildseed>Reinya Wildseed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/21/03 12:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re:what nerfs do you consider to have gone too far</span><hr size=1> MCH level is too low, however if they lower CL for non-CH the novice level seems fine in my eyes, however they need to raise novice CL or lower non-CH CL <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=juzmio>juzmio</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/21/03 1:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:what nerfs do you consider to have gone too far</span><hr size=1> I think they need to rise both novice CH and MCH.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hechicera>Hechicera</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/21/03 10:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:what nerfs do you consider to have gone too far</span><hr size=1> The lack of difference between a non-CH and a Novice is demoralizing.  <br>
<br>
I actually think that while the MCH limit is harsh, they can't fix it and if anything its too high still .. hold on ... since they have not addressed the MCH pet damage &quot;stacking&quot; with other elite Weapon skills.<br>
<br>
So a Master Pistoleer/Rifle/TKA/whatever with MCH opening up with two good pets and the full impact of the weapon will still get cries of  &quot;Unfair&quot;, even with this cap. <p>---------------------------------<br>
Motte, the newbie social cleric<br>
Xaki, evil leezard, leave her alone!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sindory>Sindory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/21/03 12:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What nerfs do you consider to have gone too far?</span><hr size=1> I agree 100% but Halo said that ch is not a combat profession (even tho it's listed as that in their guide that came with the game) it's not going to be balanced with combat professions. So this means one thing, we will keep getting nerfed. <p><a href="http://http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg"  target="blank">
Creature Handlers of SWG</a><br>The place to go for all of you Creature Handler Questions with no flames from Combat Classes!<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rorenikibi@creaturehandlersofswg>Rorenikibi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/21/03 2:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What nerfs do you consider to have gone too far?</span><hr size=1> The problem I have mentioned in a couple threads is that if we are not a combat profession, why is it our only genuine means of xp generation is, in fact, pet combat?  I've posted twice an idea for alternate xp generation and have been pretty basically ignored.  Frankly, if we are to be a support class, we need some other focus.  I've suggested twice now that pet tricks should generate XP via mind wound healing, and that we should be allowed to breed our pets, which should result in xp that way. With all the flaming and whining on the CH boards, rational discussion is lost amongst the wailing of powergamerz in withdrawal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hechicera>Hechicera</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/21/03 5:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What nerfs do you consider to have gone too far?</span><hr size=1> Maybe the hint that milk was &quot;coming&quot; (hidden in a reply somewhere - maybe bio boards) from a dev means ...<br>
<br>
... our new support role will be milking out pets.  Hope you tamed a female <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ...  it could get ugly down there.<br>
(just kidding!)<br>
<br>
I agree though.  And if we are support - what benefit to we bring to the gorup other than scenery?  And scenery that many players dislike at that (either size aka the rancor butt posts, or non star wars aka the Pet Wars Pokemon in space posts).<br>
<br>
Dancers are support too, and with great RP potential but they also provide something of significant worth in game mechanics.<br>
<br>
And actually I think he said we are half-combat.  For &quot;half-combat&quot; with no benefits (actually negatives when you factor in AI) wow thats a lot of skill points.<br>
