<br>
It is my opinion that CHs are not a support class, the only thing that they support is pet tanks nothing else unless they picked up medic like myself.<br>
<br>
In other words, i feel if they keep hitting us with that nerf bat, we will see fewer high end groups, and a whole lot more deaths in just normal groups. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg" target="top">Creature Handlers of SWG</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Pidox<br>
Master Creature Handler/Novice Pistoleer/Nocive Medic</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hechicera>Hechicera</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/22/03 7:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What nerfs do you consider to have gone too far?</span><hr size=1> I think you're right.<br>
<br>
But, I think they saw levelling and high endgroups as too easy.  And, CH pet tankage was a big part of why.  They are trying to raise the challenge of the game.<br>
<br>
Then you have the fact that PvP (from reports going back to AO guildmates that beta-ed) has always been borked and still is ... CH pets + Master Weapon skill is a hard skill to beat (esp. since CH was nerfed right before the faction pets picked up).<br>
<br>
Looking at the overall game .. I'll buy it.  But looking at the CH ... you take away half our power (leaving us underpowered unless we are medic/other weapon hybrid) and give us what?<br>
<br>
Roleplay?  Sorry, could do that already if we wanted to.<br>
<br>
Half a fighter and half a roleplay hook isn't fair game mechanic-wise to make a whole class.  Other classes can be fully effective and roleplayed too!<br>
<br>
And if you look at the majority of the non-player base.  They don't want us out there roleplaying with a turtle the size of thier house.  They want to see droids!    (can't imagine why)  =P <p>---------------------------------<br>
Mocha CH/BE Wanderhome - in retirement not cancelled</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=muerrte>Muerrte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/23/03 5:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What nerfs do you consider to have gone too far?</span><hr size=1> Hehe good points! Also if they underpower us they are going to FORCE us to take up a weapon skill and medic, even though i am already both of those cause i plan to deck out for PvP.  Still though, people shouldnt have to be forced into takeing a weapon skill.<br>
<br>
People try to bring up the fact that entertainers and crafters are forced to pick up weapons skills as well.. BS! I dont see the need for an entertainer to use a gun, what are they gonna do shoot themselves while dancing/playing music, it is not a required part of the class, those who pick up those weapon skills are the ones who dont want to be in the cantina or outside a crafting station the whole time, thats their choice.  Whereas we are going to HAVE to take a weapon skill if we want to survive.   <br>
<br>
All in all, we are getting the short end of the stick. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg" target="top">Creature Handlers of SWG</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
