<br>
Now I know it was a nerf - to cancel out an exploit.  But for those of us who were unaware it was an exploit - it was hard to start clearing out pets that I had grown fond of.  And some of those I had just tamed and was looking forward to seeing grow.<br>
<br>
I think 24 pets would be ideal for a master.  Some are our own pets - but space for the inevitable urge to tame everything in sight.  I cant overcome that after all the work to get to MCH, which involved more taming and training than killing.  And then the business side of it.  I make my living doing missions and taming and training for people - to order.  If I cant bear to part with the pets I have left - I have only 4 spare slots.  I wanted to go and explore more planets and tame many more creatures.<br>
16 slots is a pathetic number for viable business.<br>
<br>
The ration of 16 pets also affects the way we can help in groups.  I use 4 of my pets as tanks.  I am valuable part of my group because they work this way.  When damaged - they take too much healing and no one gets xp for them(another nerf)  So they have to be stored  and I lose my weapon.  My other pets are really only back up - I keep them cos I love them.  Not as helpful to the group or myself.<br>
<br>
My answer to the nerfs - give us more pets - up to 24.<br>
Have pets heal a little faster on their own, in datapad.<br>
Give healers 50% xp for healing others pets.<br>
Oh - and allow pets to be transferred in trade as well as command to transfer - I lost half my business from that bug!  People always asking me to tame and train their pets- but we couldnt trade them!!<br>
<br>
